.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DASHBOARD-INSPECT-VARS 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.8.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-dashboard\-inspect\-vars \- List dashboard templating variables and datasource\-like choices from live Grafana.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util dashboard inspect-vars [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
List dashboard templating variables and datasource\-like choices from live Grafana.
.PP
Use this when you need to inspect variable state, feed a screenshot workflow, or debug variable\-scoped dashboard URLs.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-dashboard\-uid or \-\-dashboard\-url
choose the dashboard to inspect.
.TP
.B \-\-vars\-query
overlay a variable query string such as var\-env=prod&var\-host=web01.
.TP
.B \-\-org\-id
scope the inspection to one org.
.TP
.B \-\-output\-format
render table, csv, text, json, or yaml.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-header
suppress table or CSV headers.
.TP
.B \-\-output\-file
write a copy of the output to disk.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
List dashboard templating variables and datasource\-like choices from live Grafana.
.EX
grafana-util dashboard inspect-vars --dashboard-url 'https://grafana.example.com/d/cpu-main/cpu-overview?var-cluster=prod-a' --profile prod --output-format table
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgrafana-util\fR(1),
\fBgrafana-util-dashboard\fR(1)
